Let's get a drink.

282
00:15:09,860 --> 00:15:12,640
Loser, I'll see you later.

283
00:15:12,650 --> 00:15:15,010
You asked me to go drinking.

284
00:15:15,020 --> 00:15:16,720
Which room is it?

285
00:15:19,050 --> 00:15:20,510
Why did you call him?

286
00:15:20,520 --> 00:15:22,890
I didn't. He was here, delivering pizza.

287
00:15:22,900 --> 00:15:24,090
You want to hang out with him?

288
00:15:24,100 --> 00:15:25,290
Why not?

289
00:15:25,290 --> 00:15:27,280
We used to hang out all the time, us three.

290
00:15:27,290 --> 00:15:28,620
Stop talking about that.

291
00:15:28,630 --> 00:15:30,640
I don't even remember.

292
00:15:30,650 --> 00:15:32,220
You don't, of course.

293
00:15:32,230 --> 00:15:33,450
When we were in middle school,

294
00:15:33,450 --> 00:15:37,040
you were a munchkin in first grade.

295
00:15:38,860 --> 00:15:39,850
Let's drink.

296
00:15:41,100 --> 00:15:49,140
Her hair shines through she didn't use mousse

297
00:15:49,150 --> 00:15:51,540
She looks into my eyes...

298
00:15:51,950 --> 00:15:53,280
Hey!

299
00:15:53,290 --> 00:15:54,810
This is boring.

300
00:15:54,820 --> 00:15:57,340
Yeongdal, you sing.

301
00:16:14,290 --> 00:16:17,490
Give it to me, give it to me

302
00:16:21,150 --> 00:16:24,350
Give it to me, give it to me

303
00:16:28,500 --> 00:16:31,940
I don't know if I'll get to marry

304
00:16:31,950 --> 00:16:34,740
Before I'm thirty

305
00:16:34,750 --> 00:16:38,110
I'd given my heart away

306
00:16:38,130 --> 00:16:42,020
What will I do now that it's broken?

307
00:16:43,400 --> 00:16:47,050
Amidst the rain falling blamelessly

308
00:17:10,830 --> 00:17:14,140
You should blow off some steam.

309
00:17:14,150 --> 00:17:15,550
Don't hold it all inside.

310
00:17:16,220 --> 00:17:17,410
Punch it.

311
00:17:46,600 --> 00:17:47,490
Oh, my.

312
00:17:47,490 --> 00:17:49,280
Just how much did you drink?

313
00:17:49,900 --> 00:17:51,910
He didn't, but he got drunk.

314
00:17:51,920 --> 00:17:53,480
Oh, oh.

315
00:17:53,990 --> 00:17:55,280
Was it just you two?

316
00:17:55,300 --> 00:17:57,290
With Loser.

317
00:17:57,300 --> 00:18:01,020
I want a divorce.

318
00:18:01,030 --> 00:18:05,750
Let me go! Why won't you let me go?

319
00:18:05,750 --> 00:18:08,640
Let me breathe, huh?

320
00:18:08,650 --> 00:18:11,090
Divorce me.

321
00:18:11,100 --> 00:18:14,020
Divorce me, please.

322
00:18:14,030 --> 00:18:15,620
What's he talking about?

323
00:18:15,630 --> 00:18:17,710
I think he's getting a divorce.

324
00:18:38,300 --> 00:18:39,820
Oh, that's cold!

325
00:18:39,830 --> 00:18:42,020
Aagh!

326
00:18:44,950 --> 00:18:46,010
Cold!

327
00:19:03,030 --> 00:19:04,490
Get up.

328
00:19:06,750 --> 00:19:08,310
Mom, why are you here?

329
00:19:08,330 --> 00:19:09,520
Don't you remember?

330
00:19:09,530 --> 00:19:11,620
What were you talking about last night?

331
00:19:11,630 --> 00:19:13,620
What?

332
00:19:14,150 --> 00:19:17,180
Yeongdal, get me some water.

333
00:19:17,190 --> 00:19:19,140
You're getting a divorce?

334
00:19:20,030 --> 00:19:21,820
How did you know?

335
00:19:21,830 --> 00:19:24,850
Are you really getting a divorce?

336
00:19:24,860 --> 00:19:26,410
I wish we were.

337
00:19:26,420 --> 00:19:29,210
This is nuts!

338
00:19:31,860 --> 00:19:34,780
Haebak, you must have lost of free time with your exams behind you.

339
00:19:34,800 --> 00:19:35,890
Yes.

340
00:19:35,900 --> 00:19:37,850
You did well on the exam, didn't you?

341
00:19:37,860 --> 00:19:41,020
She did. Studying comes naturally to her.

342
00:19:41,030 --> 00:19:42,690
Incredible.

343
00:19:42,690 --> 00:19:44,640
Father, can I have some money?

344
00:19:44,650 --> 00:19:46,640
I want to start going to the gym.

345
00:19:46,650 --> 00:19:47,850
The gym?

346
00:19:47,860 --> 00:19:51,620
I want to exercise and learn how to swim.

347
00:19:51,630 --> 00:19:52,980
I need to.

348
00:19:52,990 --> 00:19:55,310
Why do you need to swim?

349
00:19:55,330 --> 00:19:56,410
Knowing how to swim is a good thing.

350
00:19:56,420 --> 00:19:59,390
It can come in handy, and it's good for you.

351
00:19:59,400 --> 00:20:01,680
Don't even think about meeting any boys.

352
00:20:01,690 --> 00:20:04,390
Why not? She should go on dates.

353
00:20:04,400 --> 00:20:06,520
Studying for the bar exam is hard!

354
00:20:06,530 --> 00:20:08,420
No dating until you pass it.

355
00:20:08,420 --> 00:20:10,390
You have to pass it the first time.

356
00:20:11,250 --> 00:20:12,610
I should go to school.

357
00:20:13,060 --> 00:20:14,320
- Okay.
- I'll see you later.

358
00:20:15,600 --> 00:20:17,050
Please do it for me.

359
00:20:17,060 --> 00:20:19,450
Stay focused until you become a judge.

360
00:20:19,450 --> 00:20:23,120
I should have at least one good child.

361
00:20:24,830 --> 00:20:28,550
Bong, I have something to tell you.

362
00:20:28,560 --> 00:20:30,590
What is it?

363
00:20:30,600 --> 00:20:32,490
I have a dream.

364
00:20:32,490 --> 00:20:34,580
Incredible!

365
00:20:34,600 --> 00:20:36,850
What do you want to do?

366
00:20:36,860 --> 00:20:38,550
Open a pizza place.

367
00:20:38,560 --> 00:20:40,520
Not like any franchised ones,

368
00:20:40,530 --> 00:20:42,420
but one in my own name.

369
00:20:42,420 --> 00:20:45,140
My own, Wang's Family Pizza.

370
00:20:45,150 --> 00:20:47,890
I'm going to take classes, starting today.

371
00:20:47,900 --> 00:20:50,550
If you do a good job,

372
00:20:50,560 --> 00:20:53,820
I'll help you, even if I have to get a loan.

373
00:20:53,830 --> 00:20:55,790
But you have to be careful.

374
00:20:55,800 --> 00:20:58,090
People go out of business all the time.

375
00:20:58,100 --> 00:21:00,520
Don't take it too lightly.

376
00:21:00,530 --> 00:21:03,520
Why can't you be more encouraging?

377
00:21:03,530 --> 00:21:06,090
You'll bring bad luck.

378
00:21:06,750 --> 00:21:08,780
Subak, what are you going to do?

379
00:21:09,650 --> 00:21:10,440
Excuse me?

380
00:21:10,450 --> 00:21:13,640
You quit because the work is too hard.

381
00:21:14,360 --> 00:21:17,350
Making money isn't easy.

382
00:21:17,360 --> 00:21:20,350
So treat your husband with respect.

383
00:21:20,360 --> 00:21:22,350
Money doesn't grow on trees.

384
00:21:22,360 --> 00:21:24,350
Making money is really hard.

385
00:21:24,360 --> 00:21:25,990
Of course.

386
00:21:25,990 --> 00:21:29,240
You never earned a dime, so you don't know.

387
00:21:29,250 --> 00:21:30,680
You're not above it.

388
00:21:30,690 --> 00:21:32,440
You're an able bodied woman.

389
00:21:32,450 --> 00:21:34,390
You're not above manual labor.

390
00:21:34,400 --> 00:21:36,480
Egh, hyo, hyo, hyo, hyo.

391
00:21:36,490 --> 00:21:39,740
Don't copy me. Egh, hyo, hyo, hyo, hyo.

392
00:21:51,920 --> 00:21:53,090
Parcel service.

393
00:21:59,190 --> 00:22:01,240
I get everything delivered now,

394
00:22:01,250 --> 00:22:02,510
so I can see you.

395
00:22:02,530 --> 00:22:04,720
You're being too bold for a married woman.

396
00:22:04,720 --> 00:22:06,440
You seem to be in a good mood today.

397
00:22:06,450 --> 00:22:07,940
It's because I'm happy to see you.

398
00:22:07,950 --> 00:22:10,210
I can't help but smile these days.

399
00:22:10,220 --> 00:22:11,350
It's all because of you.

400
00:22:11,360 --> 00:22:12,910
Really?

401
00:22:13,630 --> 00:22:16,820
Come in for some tea. I made jujube tea.

402
00:22:18,530 --> 00:22:20,320
It's okay, I'm busy.

403
00:22:20,330 --> 00:22:22,640
I can't stay longer than 5 minutes per house.

404
00:22:22,650 --> 00:22:23,910
I'm glad I got to see you.

405
00:22:23,920 --> 00:22:26,010
You must be tired.

406
00:22:26,030 --> 00:22:28,720
You've never done such hard manual labor before.

407
00:22:31,150 --> 00:22:33,820
Oh, the parcel delivery guy is here.

408
00:22:33,830 --> 00:22:35,390
Isn't it cold outside?

409
00:22:35,400 --> 00:22:37,120
It is. Have a good...

410
00:22:37,130 --> 00:22:38,940
- Hold on.
- Excuse me?

411
00:22:38,950 --> 00:22:41,440
The jujube tea was good. Bring some.

412
00:22:41,450 --> 00:22:42,680
Okay.

413
00:22:42,690 --> 00:22:44,680
Oh, it's okay. I'm busy.

414
00:22:44,690 --> 00:22:48,640
Oh, please have some. It won't take long.

415
00:22:48,650 --> 00:22:50,050
It's okay.

416
00:22:51,530 --> 00:22:53,950
Oh, how odd.

417
00:22:53,950 --> 00:22:55,850
As if he was caught stealing something.

418
00:22:55,860 --> 00:22:57,590
He could've stayed for tea.

419
00:22:57,600 --> 00:22:59,320
He must be busy.

420
00:23:00,600 --> 00:23:02,990
He looked like a nice guy.

421
00:23:02,990 --> 00:23:04,740
He didn't seem like he would be doing this.

422
00:24:01,060 --> 00:24:03,750
Hi, there.

423
00:24:03,750 --> 00:24:08,340
Are you the Heo Udae I know?

424
00:24:08,360 --> 00:24:09,750
Wang Subak?

425
00:24:09,750 --> 00:24:12,910
Wow, you're alive and well?

426
00:24:12,920 --> 00:24:15,390
It's nice to see you again.

427
00:24:15,400 --> 00:24:18,020
How have you been?

428
00:24:18,900 --> 00:24:21,820
Enough small talk. Come out.

429
00:24:25,450 --> 00:24:26,940
Oh, who made you cry?

430
00:24:26,950 --> 00:24:28,850
Mom, I'll be back.

431
00:24:28,860 --> 00:24:30,820
I said I'm meeting my friends.

432
00:24:30,830 --> 00:24:32,020
I'm sorry.

433
00:24:32,030 --> 00:24:34,690
Something urgent came up. I'll be back.

434
00:24:34,690 --> 00:24:36,980
Hey! I don't...

435
00:24:37,650 --> 00:24:40,180
Oh, who made you cry?

436
00:24:48,900 --> 00:24:50,980
Oh, man!

437
00:24:50,990 --> 00:24:54,680
You look the same. It's been a long time.

438
00:24:57,920 --> 00:24:59,740
How long has it been?

439
00:24:59,750 --> 00:25:02,890
I don't remember exactly.

440
00:25:02,900 --> 00:25:05,390
When was the last time we met?

441
00:25:05,400 --> 00:25:07,740
It's been a few years.

442
00:25:07,750 --> 00:25:08,780
How many kids do you have?

443
00:25:08,800 --> 00:25:10,690
Two. A girl and a boy.

444
00:25:10,690 --> 00:25:12,850
How are your parents doing?

445
00:25:13,400 --> 00:25:15,520
They're doing fine.

446
00:25:15,530 --> 00:25:16,990
They were so mean.

447
00:25:16,990 --> 00:25:20,180
Remember how mean they were to me,

448
00:25:20,190 --> 00:25:23,140
saying I couldn't see you anymore?

449
00:25:24,030 --> 00:25:25,890
How's your little sister?

450
00:25:25,900 --> 00:25:28,140
Was her name Hobak?

451
00:25:28,150 --> 00:25:28,940
Yes.

452
00:25:28,950 --> 00:25:32,810
If it weren't for her, who knows where we'd be?

453
00:25:34,330 --> 00:25:36,620
I can't believe it happened on the day of

454
00:25:36,630 --> 00:25:39,640
the preliminary round of the pageant...

455
00:25:39,650 --> 00:25:44,510
They said I was a favorite to win,

456
00:25:44,530 --> 00:25:46,920
but I couldn't even go there.

457
00:25:46,920 --> 00:25:50,280
Now it's an old memory.

458
00:25:50,300 --> 00:25:52,120
Old memory?

459
00:25:52,130 --> 00:25:55,320
I don't even want to think about it.

460
00:25:55,690 --> 00:25:58,940
But we kept in touch behind everyone's back.

461
00:25:58,950 --> 00:26:02,390
We met a few times after you got married.

462
00:26:03,100 --> 00:26:06,590
Was it the night before your wedding?

463
00:26:06,600 --> 00:26:08,520
That was really exciting.

464
00:26:08,530 --> 00:26:10,490
Let's talk about something else.

465
00:26:10,490 --> 00:26:13,980
Because you're sorry for me? Or your husband?

466
00:26:13,990 --> 00:26:15,540
You were all into me,

467
00:26:15,560 --> 00:26:18,320
so how could you get married after 3 months?

468
00:26:18,330 --> 00:26:20,120
It wasn't because I wanted to.

469
00:26:20,130 --> 00:26:21,980
I was getting old and had no job,

470
00:26:21,990 --> 00:26:23,910
so I thought, oh, what the heck.

471
00:26:23,920 --> 00:26:25,550
You got married, too.

472
00:26:25,560 --> 00:26:27,320
I ended it soon afterwards.

473
00:26:27,330 --> 00:26:30,450
She couldn't compare to you.

474
00:26:30,450 --> 00:26:32,040
I heard your husband is doing well.

475
00:26:32,060 --> 00:26:34,590
Doing well my butt.

476
00:26:34,600 --> 00:26:37,440
His company went bankrupt.

477
00:26:37,450 --> 00:26:38,480
He's in parcel service now.

478
00:26:38,490 --> 00:26:40,120
He's in parcel service?

479
00:26:40,130 --> 00:26:43,140
Whoa, what will your parents do?

480
00:26:43,150 --> 00:26:45,790
I thought they'd find someone amazing for you.

481
00:26:47,030 --> 00:26:48,490
Wow.

482
00:26:51,690 --> 00:26:54,320
You've changed.
You're staying with him?

483
00:26:54,330 --> 00:26:56,120
But I have two kids.

484
00:26:56,130 --> 00:26:58,750
We're living with my parents. It's crazy.

485
00:26:58,750 --> 00:27:00,310
And it's no fun.

486
00:27:00,330 --> 00:27:03,390
Why don't you get out of the house?

487
00:27:03,400 --> 00:27:05,890
My company needs someone like you.

488
00:27:07,360 --> 00:27:08,890
What's this?

489
00:27:12,420 --> 00:27:15,740
That's "land," isn't it? In Chinese?

490
00:27:15,750 --> 00:27:17,890
Udae Land Development Corporation.

491
00:27:17,900 --> 00:27:19,740
CEO Heo Udae.

492
00:27:19,750 --> 00:27:21,810
Simply put, I buy and sell land.

493
00:27:21,830 --> 00:27:23,020
You're a realtor?

494
00:27:23,030 --> 00:27:24,750
It's much bigger than that.

495
00:27:24,750 --> 00:27:27,680
I'm not into renting.

496
00:27:27,690 --> 00:27:30,320
You know how I am.

497
00:27:30,330 --> 00:27:32,990
I deal in millions of dollars.

498
00:27:32,990 --> 00:27:35,580
The commission is a lot bigger.

499
00:27:35,600 --> 00:27:37,490
Wow.

500
00:27:37,490 --> 00:27:39,890
I'd like a part of that commission.

501
00:27:39,900 --> 00:27:41,820
You should follow me around.

502
00:27:41,830 --> 00:27:44,850
Your pay will be different month to month.

503
00:27:44,860 --> 00:27:46,090
When can I start?

504
00:27:46,100 --> 00:27:47,440
Tomorrow.

505
00:27:50,860 --> 00:27:52,120
Here.

506
00:27:57,690 --> 00:28:00,680
Get a nice suit.

507
00:28:01,450 --> 00:28:03,310
Is this an advance?

508
00:28:03,330 --> 00:28:06,640
I can't believe you'd even ask that.

509
00:28:06,650 --> 00:28:08,390
This is like a bonus.

510
00:28:08,400 --> 00:28:10,680
Your pay will depend on how you do.

511
00:28:10,690 --> 00:28:13,890
It can be tens or hundreds of thousand dollars.

512
00:28:13,900 --> 00:28:15,620
Oh, my!

513
00:28:16,330 --> 00:28:17,550
I have to go.

514
00:28:17,560 --> 00:28:19,250
Look nice tomorrow.

515
00:28:19,250 --> 00:28:22,940
Tell people you were in the final round.

516
00:28:22,950 --> 00:28:25,240
You know me better than anyone in the world.

517
00:28:25,250 --> 00:28:27,180
Of course.

518
00:28:31,190 --> 00:28:32,620
It's me.

519
00:28:32,630 --> 00:28:34,640
I got the 2 million dollars yesterday.

520
00:28:34,650 --> 00:28:36,790
Send me 5 million by this weekend.

521
00:28:36,800 --> 00:28:39,620
Let's make it 10.

522
00:28:39,630 --> 00:28:41,750
We should grab a drink sometime.

523
00:28:41,750 --> 00:28:43,980
Or play golf.

524
00:28:51,100 --> 00:28:52,220
It's two dollars.

525
00:28:52,220 --> 00:28:54,410
Oh, wait, let me see.

526
00:28:54,420 --> 00:28:56,180
I have some dollar bills.

527
00:28:57,300 --> 00:28:58,450
Keep the change.

528
00:28:58,450 --> 00:29:00,680
Thank you, sir. Thank you.

529
00:29:07,150 --> 00:29:09,350
I'd drive you home, but I'm busy.

530
00:29:09,360 --> 00:29:11,710
It's okay. I'll see you tomorrow.

531
00:29:11,720 --> 00:29:12,640
Okay.

532
00:29:23,600 --> 00:29:25,390
Mom! Mom!

533
00:29:27,250 --> 00:29:28,610
You got a job?

534
00:29:28,630 --> 00:29:30,620
Yes, I start tomorrow.

535
00:29:31,420 --> 00:29:33,050
What do they do?

536
00:29:33,060 --> 00:29:34,990
It's a really nice company.

537
00:29:34,990 --> 00:29:37,580
It's like every hair on my body has come alive.

538
00:29:37,600 --> 00:29:40,410
Every hair on your body?

539
00:29:40,420 --> 00:29:41,850
That happens when you're cold.

540
00:29:41,860 --> 00:29:44,090
I mean I feel amazing.

541
00:29:44,100 --> 00:29:45,520
It's "effing" amazing!

542
00:29:45,530 --> 00:29:47,490
Why would you say that?

543
00:29:47,490 --> 00:29:49,010
You're a mom.

544
00:29:49,030 --> 00:29:50,890
If your father heard you, he'd be mad.

545
00:29:51,860 --> 00:29:53,940
Anyway, I start tomorrow.

546
00:29:53,950 --> 00:29:55,410
What about the kids?

547
00:29:55,420 --> 00:29:57,410
You have to take care of them.

548
00:29:57,420 --> 00:29:59,510
I didn't make it to my meeting today.

549
00:29:59,530 --> 00:30:01,320
I'll give you money, mom.

550
00:30:01,330 --> 00:30:02,910
I'll pay you for babysitting.

551
00:30:02,920 --> 00:30:04,590
It's getting harder every year.

552
00:30:04,600 --> 00:30:08,520
I'm old and it's hard for me.

553
00:30:09,100 --> 00:30:10,890
I'm afraid to take care of them.

554
00:30:10,900 --> 00:30:12,410
Where is Gwangbak?

555
00:30:12,420 --> 00:30:14,590
Why can't she babysit?

556
00:30:35,560 --> 00:30:36,910
Did you wait long?

557
00:30:40,420 --> 00:30:41,980
What is it?

558
00:30:41,990 --> 00:30:43,180
Well...

559
00:30:43,190 --> 00:30:45,510
have you ever experienced this?

560
00:30:45,530 --> 00:30:48,350
You see a person walking towards you,

