00:30:48,360 --> 00:30:51,390
and you see a halo like this,

562
00:30:51,400 --> 00:30:54,520
like a big moon, shining brightly.

563
00:30:54,530 --> 00:30:56,320
Like in paintings of Jesus,

564
00:30:56,330 --> 00:30:59,720
he has this halo behind his head.

565
00:30:59,720 --> 00:31:00,910
It was just like that.

566
00:31:00,920 --> 00:31:02,590
You saw my halo?

567
00:31:02,600 --> 00:31:05,410
Oh, carrying that was a lot of work.

568
00:31:05,420 --> 00:31:08,320
I'm hungry. Here. 
Rock, paper, scissors!

569
00:31:09,530 --> 00:31:10,220
What was that?

570
00:31:10,220 --> 00:31:12,480
You're cooking the meat! Lets go in.

571
00:31:19,250 --> 00:31:21,140
Yummy.

572
00:31:21,150 --> 00:31:23,010
You're good at this.

573
00:31:24,860 --> 00:31:26,410
Oh!

574
00:31:26,420 --> 00:31:27,980
It's really delicious.

575
00:31:34,400 --> 00:31:36,090
You're really good at this.

576
00:31:52,130 --> 00:31:55,410
Oh, that was good.

577
00:31:58,130 --> 00:32:00,090
I'm done. Let's go.

578
00:32:00,100 --> 00:32:02,050
- What?
- Let's go.

579
00:32:02,060 --> 00:32:03,750
This can't be.

580
00:32:03,750 --> 00:32:07,310
Why are you crying all of a sudden?

581
00:32:07,330 --> 00:32:09,790
I didn't get to eat anything!

582
00:32:09,800 --> 00:32:10,920
What were you doing?

583
00:32:10,920 --> 00:32:12,320
You told me to grill the pork.

584
00:32:12,330 --> 00:32:15,490
You said I'm it, so I have to do this!

585
00:32:16,220 --> 00:32:18,010
I'm not going to marry you.

586
00:32:18,030 --> 00:32:18,750
What?

587
00:32:18,750 --> 00:32:21,040
If I married such an inconsiderate man,

588
00:32:21,060 --> 00:32:23,220
I'd starve to death.

589
00:32:23,220 --> 00:32:25,810
I'm starving, but you ate alone.

590
00:32:25,830 --> 00:32:28,820
I waited to see if you'd give me a bite,

591
00:32:28,830 --> 00:32:30,320
but you didn't.

592
00:32:30,330 --> 00:32:33,590
And now that you're full, you want to go.

593
00:32:33,600 --> 00:32:36,590
I didn't know you were like this.

594
00:32:40,030 --> 00:32:41,520
Excuse me!

595
00:32:41,530 --> 00:32:46,710
Can we get a new grill and two portions of pork belly?

596
00:32:54,990 --> 00:32:56,580
Eat.

597
00:32:57,220 --> 00:33:01,480
I was testing you, and you fell for it.

598
00:33:01,490 --> 00:33:03,280
You're so simple minded.

599
00:33:04,030 --> 00:33:06,290
You were testing me?

600
00:33:06,300 --> 00:33:09,290
If I don't have any income,

601
00:33:09,300 --> 00:33:12,290
you'd pack up and leave me.

602
00:33:12,300 --> 00:33:15,590
Just because you didn't get to eat,

603
00:33:15,600 --> 00:33:18,890
you called me inconsiderate.

604
00:33:18,900 --> 00:33:22,210
I can't believe my own wife would call me that.

605
00:33:23,150 --> 00:33:26,120
Are you going to call me that again?

606
00:33:26,130 --> 00:33:27,640
I won't.

607
00:33:27,650 --> 00:33:30,320
What do you think about how you acted?

608
00:33:30,330 --> 00:33:32,090
I'm sorry.

609
00:33:32,930 --> 00:33:35,250
You really think I'd eat it all by myself?

610
00:33:35,260 --> 00:33:38,390
If you'd won, I would've grilled the pork.

611
00:33:38,400 --> 00:33:41,040
I was just trying to be funny,

612
00:33:41,050 --> 00:33:43,390
but you have no sense of humor.

613
00:33:43,400 --> 00:33:47,580
You don't have an ounce of patience!

614
00:33:48,950 --> 00:33:50,540
Eat slowly.

615
00:33:50,550 --> 00:33:52,640
I told you, from now on...

616
00:33:52,660 --> 00:33:54,350
Eat only the meat I buy you,

617
00:33:54,360 --> 00:33:56,390
eat only the meat I grill for you,

618
00:33:56,400 --> 00:33:58,580
and eat only the meat I wrap for you.

619
00:33:58,590 --> 00:33:59,740
Got it?

620
00:33:59,760 --> 00:34:00,980
Good girl.

621
00:34:15,590 --> 00:34:16,910
Is it good?

622
00:34:17,990 --> 00:34:20,910
Because you grilled it, it's so, so good.

623
00:34:20,930 --> 00:34:22,520
Don't say so, so.

624
00:34:35,450 --> 00:34:38,680
Oh, no! Oh, no! Fire! Fire!

625
00:34:45,260 --> 00:34:47,050
What do I do?

626
00:34:47,050 --> 00:34:47,980
Oh, no!

627
00:34:50,130 --> 00:34:51,150
Hi.

628
00:34:52,050 --> 00:34:53,540
Hello.

629
00:34:54,990 --> 00:34:56,290
Here.

630
00:34:56,860 --> 00:34:59,390
Thank you. Thank you so much.

631
00:34:59,400 --> 00:35:00,690
Good luck.

632
00:35:18,760 --> 00:35:20,190
You got a job?

633
00:35:20,200 --> 00:35:22,020
She starts tomorrow.

634
00:35:22,030 --> 00:35:23,440
Where is it?

635
00:35:23,450 --> 00:35:25,980
It's some land developing company.

636
00:35:25,990 --> 00:35:28,310
They'll pay me a lot, depending on how I do.

637
00:35:28,320 --> 00:35:30,180
There are a lot of grifters in that field.

638
00:35:30,200 --> 00:35:31,490
You should do some research.

639
00:35:31,490 --> 00:35:34,080
He's not a grifter. I can trust him.

640
00:35:34,090 --> 00:35:35,810
You don't know what you're talking about.

641
00:35:35,820 --> 00:35:37,480
I know the CEO,

642
00:35:37,490 --> 00:35:38,810
and he gave me the job.

643
00:35:38,820 --> 00:35:42,120
He gave her $5,000 as an advance,

644
00:35:42,130 --> 00:35:44,210
so she could buy some clothes.

645
00:35:44,220 --> 00:35:46,890
The company must be very solid.

646
00:35:46,900 --> 00:35:48,980
He gave you $5,000?

647
00:35:48,990 --> 00:35:51,680
Yes, he believes in me.

648
00:35:51,700 --> 00:35:52,590
Why would he?

649
00:35:52,590 --> 00:35:54,540
You don't know how to do anything.

650
00:35:54,550 --> 00:35:57,980
She looks good just standing there.

651
00:35:57,990 --> 00:35:59,540
Who would pay you to just stand there?

652
00:35:59,550 --> 00:36:02,710
Hey, I would love to have that job.

653
00:36:03,400 --> 00:36:07,440
The real estate market is really bad,

654
00:36:07,450 --> 00:36:09,410
but it's okay to try different things.

655
00:36:09,430 --> 00:36:15,010
Work hard for your family and for the country's economy.

656
00:36:15,030 --> 00:36:18,290
You'll meet lots of people in that field,

657
00:36:18,300 --> 00:36:20,320
and I think it would be perfect for you.

658
00:36:20,320 --> 00:36:21,410
I won't disappoint you.

659
00:36:21,430 --> 00:36:24,650
I'm going to become a working mom.

660
00:36:24,660 --> 00:36:26,650
Don't forget to pay me for raising your kids.

661
00:36:26,660 --> 00:36:30,120
Now that you got a job, you should.

662
00:36:36,220 --> 00:36:37,790
What are you doing?

663
00:36:37,800 --> 00:36:39,480
Stay still.

664
00:36:40,950 --> 00:36:44,580
Subak, I'm sorry.

665
00:36:44,590 --> 00:36:47,440
I didn't want you to get a job.

666
00:36:47,450 --> 00:36:49,350
I know you love it.

667
00:36:49,360 --> 00:36:51,310
I don't.

668
00:36:51,320 --> 00:36:55,780
If I could, I wouldn't want you to work.

669
00:36:55,800 --> 00:36:57,290
It's okay.

670
00:36:57,300 --> 00:36:59,790
It's about time I got a job.

671
00:37:00,900 --> 00:37:02,520
Won't it be too much?

672
00:37:02,530 --> 00:37:04,350
Even if it is, I have to do it.

673
00:37:04,360 --> 00:37:07,080
Oh, why can't I open this?

674
00:37:08,530 --> 00:37:11,120
I met your brother in laws.

675
00:37:11,130 --> 00:37:14,120
Should I take your sisters out for dinner?

676
00:37:14,590 --> 00:37:17,410
It's okay. You don't have to.

677
00:37:17,430 --> 00:37:19,020
But I want to earn points.

678
00:37:19,030 --> 00:37:22,350
You already earned lots of points.

679
00:37:23,720 --> 00:37:25,940
Oh, the fish I sent before,

680
00:37:25,950 --> 00:37:27,810
they don't sell them anywhere.

681
00:37:27,820 --> 00:37:30,440
My company does business with them,

682
00:37:30,450 --> 00:37:32,680
so when you run out, let me know.

683
00:37:33,590 --> 00:37:35,010
Don't worry about it.

684
00:37:35,030 --> 00:37:37,850
You already sent too much stuff.

685
00:37:37,860 --> 00:37:39,980
I haven't been able to do anything for you.

686
00:37:43,200 --> 00:37:46,120
Oh, the night air is chilly.

687
00:37:46,130 --> 00:37:47,390
You're not cold?

688
00:37:47,990 --> 00:37:49,580
I get cold easily,

689
00:37:49,590 --> 00:37:51,620
but being here with you,

690
00:37:51,630 --> 00:37:53,580
I don't feel cold at all.

691
00:37:53,590 --> 00:37:56,980
Liar. Your lips are blue.

692
00:37:56,990 --> 00:38:00,020
No, no, I'm okay.

693
00:38:03,300 --> 00:38:05,890
Don't fart in front of him.

694
00:38:05,900 --> 00:38:09,020
If you feel one coming when you're with him,

695
00:38:09,030 --> 00:38:11,690
start clapping really loudly.

696
00:38:14,530 --> 00:38:17,050
I see stars.

697
00:38:19,720 --> 00:38:22,480
Autumn night is very picturesque.

698
00:38:23,220 --> 00:38:25,520
Autumn is the man's season.

699
00:38:27,050 --> 00:38:28,580
Do you know what autumn smells like?

700
00:38:33,260 --> 00:38:36,440
How funny! Autumn doesn't smell!

701
00:38:36,450 --> 00:38:38,310
So funny!

702
00:38:38,320 --> 00:38:39,910
I didn't say anything funny.

703
00:38:39,930 --> 00:38:41,550
The smell of autumn is funny?

704
00:38:41,550 --> 00:38:43,350
It's so funny.

705
00:38:43,360 --> 00:38:45,290
Oh, my stomach.

706
00:38:49,030 --> 00:38:51,290
This is a children's playground,

707
00:38:51,300 --> 00:38:53,590
so you shouldn't pollute it like this.

708
00:38:53,590 --> 00:38:55,780
You hid the sound well,

709
00:38:55,800 --> 00:38:59,050
but I guess you didn't learn to rid the smell.

710
00:38:59,990 --> 00:39:03,080
Oh, no! Oh, no!

711
00:39:06,990 --> 00:39:08,910
Good night, my sweet sucker!

712
00:39:12,320 --> 00:39:13,210
What is it?

713
00:39:15,700 --> 00:39:17,120
Well,

714
00:39:17,860 --> 00:39:21,120
please don't tell him the family is opposed of us.

715
00:39:21,130 --> 00:39:22,650
I haven't told him.

716
00:39:22,660 --> 00:39:24,050
What are you going to do?

717
00:39:24,050 --> 00:39:25,850
Mom and dad are really against him.

718
00:39:25,860 --> 00:39:27,750
I'm going to change their mind.

719
00:39:27,760 --> 00:39:29,710
He's a good man.

720
00:39:29,720 --> 00:39:33,680
I know, so don't ever tell him.

721
00:39:41,820 --> 00:39:43,010
Can we talk?

722
00:39:50,450 --> 00:39:52,140
Hey, you.

723
00:39:52,160 --> 00:39:54,750
Hey, how could you run home like that?

724
00:39:54,760 --> 00:39:57,790
I had to clean the mess you left.

725
00:39:58,430 --> 00:39:59,890
I won't ever do that to you again.

726
00:39:59,900 --> 00:40:02,710
So delete that from your memory, please.

727
00:40:02,720 --> 00:40:04,140
I'll think about it.

728
00:40:04,660 --> 00:40:06,790
I'll be good to you.

729
00:40:06,800 --> 00:40:08,320
Would you like to video chat?

730
00:40:09,130 --> 00:40:10,920
No, I look awful right now.

731
00:40:10,930 --> 00:40:12,390
I can't show you my bare face.

732
00:40:12,900 --> 00:40:15,480
You've been wearing makeup?

733
00:40:15,490 --> 00:40:17,210
I hate you.

734
00:40:18,050 --> 00:40:21,210
Gwangbak! Can I get some sleep?

735
00:40:21,220 --> 00:40:22,440
Sorry.

736
00:40:23,200 --> 00:40:24,290
I'm sorry.

737
00:40:26,200 --> 00:40:28,150
This is my room.

738
00:40:29,160 --> 00:40:31,390
This is my library.

739
00:40:32,360 --> 00:40:34,120
And this is the bedroom side.

740
00:40:34,950 --> 00:40:36,390
This is our bed.

741
00:40:36,400 --> 00:40:39,040
I mean, it's my bed.

742
00:40:39,930 --> 00:40:42,090
It's a really nice house.

743
00:40:42,090 --> 00:40:44,350
It's so much nicer than my house.

744
00:41:00,220 --> 00:41:04,120
I don't feel hungry anymore these days.

745
00:41:04,860 --> 00:41:06,310
You're such a liar!

746
00:41:06,320 --> 00:41:08,780
Remember how much pork you ate tonight?

747
00:41:08,800 --> 00:41:12,350
I'll have to make lots of money just to feed you.

748
00:41:12,360 --> 00:41:15,350
No, you won't. I don't eat much.

749
00:41:15,360 --> 00:41:17,790
You can't call that "not much."

750
00:41:17,800 --> 00:41:21,420
2 portions of pork and a bowl of rice and soup?

751
00:41:21,430 --> 00:41:23,750
And you ate noodles, too.

752
00:41:23,760 --> 00:41:24,940
You call that "not much"?

753
00:41:24,950 --> 00:41:26,680
You eat like me, a manual laborer!

754
00:41:27,700 --> 00:41:29,450
That's how much I ate?

755
00:41:29,450 --> 00:41:31,120
Oh, no.

756
00:41:32,260 --> 00:41:35,290
Eat up. Eat a lot and get fat.

757
00:41:35,300 --> 00:41:37,590
I'm sure I'll make enough money to feed you.

758
00:41:38,430 --> 00:41:40,290
How nice! I'm so happy.

759
00:41:40,300 --> 00:41:41,890
I don't have to worry about food, do I?

760
00:41:41,900 --> 00:41:43,440
I'm going to get fat.

761
00:41:44,860 --> 00:41:46,210
Hey,

762
00:41:46,220 --> 00:41:50,580
do you still think of me when you wake up?

763
00:41:50,590 --> 00:41:52,620
I think of you before I go to sleep,

764
00:41:52,630 --> 00:41:54,650
I think of you while sleeping,

765
00:41:54,660 --> 00:41:58,150
and whenever I toss and turn, you pop up.

766
00:41:58,160 --> 00:41:59,720
Do you think of me?

767
00:41:59,720 --> 00:42:00,810
I'm a manual laborer, so...

768
00:42:00,820 --> 00:42:02,040
Okay, okay.

769
00:42:02,050 --> 00:42:05,710
So when you fall asleep, you don't wake up.

770
00:42:06,860 --> 00:42:09,520
How many times a day do you think of me?

771
00:42:09,530 --> 00:42:10,980
Just twice?

772
00:42:10,990 --> 00:42:13,080
No, no!

773
00:42:13,090 --> 00:42:15,710
I think about you all day.

774
00:42:16,220 --> 00:42:18,180
For me, it's quality over quantity.

775
00:42:18,200 --> 00:42:20,690
I think of you twice a day, very seriously.

776
00:42:20,700 --> 00:42:22,190
You do?

777
00:42:25,400 --> 00:42:27,540
I'm not sleepy yet.

778
00:42:27,550 --> 00:42:30,640
I want to talk to you all night.

779
00:42:30,660 --> 00:42:34,820
Why don't you stay up all night with me?

780
00:42:34,820 --> 00:42:36,210
Please let me sleep! Please!

781
00:42:36,220 --> 00:42:38,680
Are you trying to torture me?

782
00:42:40,760 --> 00:42:42,190
Who's that?

783
00:42:44,700 --> 00:42:47,020
My uncle. He was awake.

784
00:42:47,030 --> 00:42:50,080
He asked me if I'm trying to torture him.

785
00:42:52,720 --> 00:42:54,290
I should get you out of there soon.

786
00:42:54,300 --> 00:42:57,550
I can't even talk to you in peace.

787
00:42:57,550 --> 00:42:59,010
Let's do this before the end of this year.

788
00:42:59,030 --> 00:43:02,550
Let's set a date after you meet my father.

789
00:43:04,450 --> 00:43:06,020
Before the end of this year?

790
00:43:06,030 --> 00:43:09,820
Can we take it slowly?

791
00:43:10,430 --> 00:43:12,920
But you're the one who wanted to rush this.

792
00:43:13,700 --> 00:43:15,120
I know.

793
00:43:16,860 --> 00:43:20,290
Put on a coat and a scarf when you go out.

794
00:43:20,300 --> 00:43:22,440
It's pretty chilly outside.

795
00:43:24,550 --> 00:43:26,210
You're outside?

796
00:43:26,220 --> 00:43:27,810
I'm going to the construction site.

797
00:43:27,820 --> 00:43:29,810
You're driving?

798
00:43:29,820 --> 00:43:32,540
Of course. For a while now.

799
00:43:32,550 --> 00:43:35,440
Oh, no, I didn't know you were driving.

800
00:43:35,450 --> 00:43:37,910
I thought you were in your room.

801
00:43:37,930 --> 00:43:40,150
I can't talk on the phone while driving.

802
00:43:40,160 --> 00:43:44,090
My voice goes up and I can't talk nicely.

803
00:43:44,090 --> 00:43:46,390
How can you drive so well?

804
00:43:46,400 --> 00:43:48,210
Have you ever seen a player who can't drive?

805
00:43:49,550 --> 00:43:51,440
Are you there yet?

806
00:43:51,450 --> 00:43:54,250
Yes, I'm here.

807
00:43:54,260 --> 00:43:57,820
They are all ready to start working.

808
00:44:00,660 --> 00:44:02,020
What time is it?

809
00:44:02,030 --> 00:44:03,750
The newspaper is here.

810
00:44:03,760 --> 00:44:05,550
So we talked all night.

811
00:44:05,550 --> 00:44:06,940
Write it in your journal.

812
00:44:07,860 --> 00:44:09,790
I'm going to start now.

813
00:44:09,800 --> 00:44:12,420
Okay. Be safe.

814
00:44:12,430 --> 00:44:14,720
You can't get hurt.

815
00:44:14,720 --> 00:44:17,210
If you're hurt, you can't take care of me.

816
00:44:17,220 --> 00:44:18,250
Okay.

817
00:44:18,260 --> 00:44:21,350
Go to bed. I have to work to feed you.

818
00:44:21,360 --> 00:44:22,420
Give me a kiss!

819
00:44:22,430 --> 00:44:23,450
Kiss!

820
00:44:33,160 --> 00:44:35,790
Were you on the phone all night?

821
00:44:35,800 --> 00:44:36,820
Yes.

822
00:44:36,820 --> 00:44:39,480
I'm sorry I kept you awake, uncle.

823
00:44:39,490 --> 00:44:40,750
Gwangbak,

824
00:44:41,860 --> 00:44:44,690
I don't mind being awake,

825
00:44:44,700 --> 00:44:49,190
and I'm happy you're in a relationship.

826
00:44:49,200 --> 00:44:51,420
I know it's not in my place,

827
00:44:51,430 --> 00:44:54,390
and I can pretend not to know anything...

828
00:44:54,400 --> 00:44:56,290
I know, uncle.

829
00:44:57,130 --> 00:44:59,850
Break up with him before your parents find out.

830
00:44:59,860 --> 00:45:01,040
It'll only get harder for you.

831
00:45:29,160 --> 00:45:31,090
He doesn't want you.

832
00:45:31,090 --> 00:45:32,910
Why do you want to stay married?

833
00:45:33,630 --> 00:45:35,580
- Mother.
- What?

834
00:45:35,590 --> 00:45:38,480
Must you say this so early in the morning?

835
00:45:38,490 --> 00:45:40,540
Why do you think I came?

836
00:45:40,550 --> 00:45:42,740
Sedal came to my house all drunk.

837
00:45:42,760 --> 00:45:47,580
He drinks every night and comes to my house saying he hates you.

838
00:45:47,590 --> 00:45:49,510
How could you say such a mean thing?

839
00:45:49,530 --> 00:45:51,350
You're a woman, too!

840
00:45:51,360 --> 00:45:53,690
When Sedal talks nonsense like that,

841
00:45:53,700 --> 00:45:56,450
you should kick some sense into him.

842
00:45:56,450 --> 00:45:58,810
You said Sedal will become the president.

843
00:45:58,820 --> 00:46:01,640
Who knows what your grandsons will become?

844
00:46:01,660 --> 00:46:03,590
If you don't want to end up at a hearing,

845
00:46:03,590 --> 00:46:04,640
you should talk to him.

846
00:46:04,660 --> 00:46:06,990
Who cares about any hearing?

847
00:46:06,990 --> 00:46:09,520
I agree with everything my son says,

848
00:46:09,530 --> 00:46:11,420
and I'm always on his side.

849
00:46:11,430 --> 00:46:14,950
I didn't want you as my son's wife,

850
00:46:14,950 --> 00:46:17,540
but I said yes because he wanted you.

851
00:46:17,550 --> 00:46:19,680
And the same will go for the divorce.

852
00:46:19,700 --> 00:46:22,190
You have sons, so why can't you understand?

853
00:46:22,200 --> 00:46:23,820
If Sintong and Bangtong told you

854
00:46:23,820 --> 00:46:26,390
they'd rather die than stay with their wives,

855
00:46:26,400 --> 00:46:29,190
would you tell them to die?

856
00:46:29,200 --> 00:46:32,220
"Put yourself in his shoes" is your family motto.

857
00:46:32,220 --> 00:46:34,850
Let's say you met an amazing man.

858
00:46:34,860 --> 00:46:38,350
How would you feel if Sedal wouldn't let you go?

859
00:46:38,360 --> 00:46:42,940
You'd kick him off and go your way.

860
00:46:44,800 --> 00:46:47,020
I don't even want to answer that.

861
00:46:48,200 --> 00:46:50,950
You should go. I have to go to work.

862
00:46:50,950 --> 00:46:54,350
Think about what you did to Sedal.

863
00:46:54,360 --> 00:46:56,890
You treated him like dirt because you work,

864
00:46:56,900 --> 00:46:59,250
and how did you treat me and Yeongdal?

865
00:46:59,260 --> 00:47:02,440
Even that rich women fell for my son,

866
00:47:02,450 --> 00:47:04,350
so how dare you treat him so badly?

867
00:47:04,360 --> 00:47:06,710
I knew this day would come.

868
00:47:07,700 --> 00:47:09,190
Mother.

869
00:47:09,760 --> 00:47:12,450
He wouldn't cheat on you if you were good to him.

870
00:47:12,450 --> 00:47:16,810
I can't believe you gave him $3 a day and beat him up every day.

871
00:47:16,820 --> 00:47:18,740
Stop that, please!

872
00:47:18,760 --> 00:47:22,250
Sedal and I are married.

873
00:47:22,260 --> 00:47:24,190
So you stay out of this.

874
00:47:24,200 --> 00:47:25,820
Just think of it as your fate.

875
00:47:25,820 --> 00:47:28,480
I didn't want to be a widow.

876
00:47:28,490 --> 00:47:30,750
I just accepted it because it happened.

877
00:47:50,720 --> 00:47:52,180
Where to?

878
00:47:52,200 --> 00:47:54,890
The department store.
 I need to go shopping for our trip.

879
00:47:54,900 --> 00:47:56,420
Okay.

880
00:47:59,700 --> 00:48:00,820
Oh, oh, my god!

881
00:48:00,820 --> 00:48:03,620
She scared me! What's wrong with her?

882
00:48:10,720 --> 00:48:12,210
Why are you doing this?

883
00:48:12,220 --> 00:48:13,680
I'm sick and tired of you.

884
00:48:13,700 --> 00:48:15,390
We need to talk.

885
00:48:15,400 --> 00:48:17,810
I'm working. Can't you see?

886
00:48:17,820 --> 00:48:18,890
Quit!

887
00:48:19,490 --> 00:48:20,180
What?

888
00:48:20,200 --> 00:48:22,950
Quit this stupid job!

889
00:48:25,090 --> 00:48:26,710
Let's go. Let's talk.

890
00:48:35,030 --> 00:48:37,210
Why did you tell your mother?

891
00:48:37,220 --> 00:48:39,440
Now my family will find out.

892
00:48:39,450 --> 00:48:41,080
What are you trying to do here?

893
00:48:41,090 --> 00:48:43,680
I'm trying to get a divorce here.

894
00:48:43,700 --> 00:48:45,190
You don't feel guilty?

895
00:48:45,200 --> 00:48:46,590
I do.

896
00:48:46,590 --> 00:48:49,280
I know I did nothing for you.

897
00:48:49,300 --> 00:48:51,050
Then why do you want a divorce?

898
00:48:51,050 --> 00:48:53,540
I feel guilty so let's get a divorce.

899
00:48:55,220 --> 00:48:57,440
If you really love her, go.

900
00:48:57,450 --> 00:48:58,910
Go to her, but

901
00:48:58,930 --> 00:49:01,050
come back when you think it was a mistake.

902
00:49:01,700 --> 00:49:04,390
Really? For real?

903
00:49:04,950 --> 00:49:07,250
I'd like to say that,

904
00:49:07,260 --> 00:49:09,590
but I'm not that open minded.

905
00:49:09,590 --> 00:49:11,620
Why you... Are you playing with me?

906
00:49:11,630 --> 00:49:14,650
You owe me a lot, so you can't divorce me.

907
00:49:14,660 --> 00:49:17,450
If I divorce you, I'd regret it.

908
00:49:17,450 --> 00:49:19,250
You said you feel guilty.

909
00:49:19,260 --> 00:49:22,520
Then stay by my side until you die.

910
00:49:22,530 --> 00:49:24,690
Die on my lap!

911
00:49:24,700 --> 00:49:26,620
This is nuts.

912
00:49:26,630 --> 00:49:28,390
How many more times must I tell you?

913
00:49:28,400 --> 00:49:30,710
Even if I wanted to, I can't stay with you!

914
00:49:30,720 --> 00:49:32,620
You're not a woman to me.

915
00:49:32,630 --> 00:49:36,120
You're like a piece of log!

916
00:49:39,720 --> 00:49:44,020
I'm like a piece of log?

917
00:49:44,030 --> 00:49:46,980
Yes. That's all I have to say.

918
00:49:46,990 --> 00:49:50,520
This is making you more pathetic, you know?

919
00:49:57,820 --> 00:50:00,440
Sedal! Sedal!

920
00:50:00,450 --> 00:50:03,540
Don't! Don't go. Let's talk.

921
00:50:03,550 --> 00:50:05,080
Stop this!

922
00:50:28,990 --> 00:50:31,080
You're not a woman to me anymore.

923
00:50:31,090 --> 00:50:34,210
You're like a nagging older sister,

924
00:50:34,220 --> 00:50:36,910
and you make me feel little!

925
00:50:36,930 --> 00:50:40,490
You're like a piece of log, okay?

926
00:50:51,400 --> 00:50:52,150
Get in.

927
00:50:52,160 --> 00:50:53,550
Hi!

928
00:52:04,130 --> 00:52:05,710
Yay! New clothes!

929
00:52:05,720 --> 00:52:09,180
Finally, I got new clothes! How exciting!

930
00:52:09,760 --> 00:52:11,020
Now.

931
00:52:11,300 --> 00:52:12,790
Sit down.

932
00:52:13,550 --> 00:52:15,240
What is it, mom?

933
00:52:15,860 --> 00:52:17,710
Are you going to yell at us again?

934
00:52:17,720 --> 00:52:19,710
I'm not.

935
00:52:21,320 --> 00:52:24,280
Mom's going somewhere.

936
00:52:24,300 --> 00:52:25,750
Where?

937
00:52:26,490 --> 00:52:29,120
Somewhere far away.

938
00:52:29,130 --> 00:52:32,940
Do you want to stay or come with me?

939
00:52:32,950 --> 00:52:35,080
Where are you going?

940
00:52:35,090 --> 00:52:36,180
I'm coming with you.

941
00:52:36,200 --> 00:52:38,750
Bangtong, you come, too.

942
00:52:38,760 --> 00:52:40,120
Is dad coming, too?

943
00:52:40,130 --> 00:52:41,580
Dad's not coming.

944
00:52:41,590 --> 00:52:42,940
It's just the three of us.

945
00:52:44,130 --> 00:52:45,480
Do you want to come with me?

946
00:52:50,450 --> 00:52:51,540
Get in.

947
00:52:52,130 --> 00:52:53,480
Is this our car?

948
00:52:53,490 --> 00:52:54,350
Yes.

949
00:52:54,360 --> 00:52:56,690
I bought it for you guys.

950
00:52:56,700 --> 00:52:58,190
How exciting!

951
00:52:58,200 --> 00:52:59,590
Mom, you're the best!

952
00:52:59,590 --> 00:53:02,280
We have a car! How exciting!

953
00:53:08,800 --> 00:53:11,980
Mom, mom, I wish dad would come with us.

954
00:53:11,990 --> 00:53:14,180
Can't you see what's going on?

955
00:53:14,200 --> 00:53:16,550
Why would you talk about dad now?

956
00:53:16,550 --> 00:53:19,140
Look how upset she looks.

957
00:53:19,160 --> 00:53:21,250
Why aren't we taking dad?

958
00:53:21,260 --> 00:53:22,420
Get in.

959
00:53:34,490 --> 00:53:37,680
I'm not responsible for anything that happens.

960
00:53:41,300 --> 00:53:44,150
The phone is turned off...

961
00:53:44,160 --> 00:53:45,790
Oh, man.

962
00:53:46,820 --> 00:53:48,080
The phone is turned off...

963
00:53:48,090 --> 00:53:50,040
This is nuts.

964
00:53:50,800 --> 00:53:52,150
What is it?

965
00:53:52,700 --> 00:53:54,750
I need to go home.

966
00:53:54,760 --> 00:53:57,150
What is it? We have to go now.

967
00:53:58,160 --> 00:53:59,290
Just hold on.

968
00:53:59,300 --> 00:54:01,920
I don't want anything bad to happen.

969
00:54:01,930 --> 00:54:03,620
I'll be right back.

970
00:54:11,450 --> 00:54:13,540
Hey! Where are you? Hey!

971
00:54:13,550 --> 00:54:16,410
Sintong! Bangtong!

972
00:54:18,700 --> 00:54:19,750
How dare you...

973
00:54:26,590 --> 00:54:30,850
Your call will be forwarded to voice message.

974
00:54:30,860 --> 00:54:32,520
This is nuts.

975
00:54:42,260 --> 00:54:43,390
What is it?

976
00:54:43,400 --> 00:54:45,620
Mom, are the boys with you?

977
00:54:45,630 --> 00:54:47,190
No, why?

978
00:54:47,200 --> 00:54:49,910
There's no one home, and she won't answer the phone.

979
00:54:49,930 --> 00:54:52,650
I called her office and she's on vacation.

980
00:54:52,660 --> 00:54:55,820
Where did she go? She took the boys?

981
00:54:55,820 --> 00:54:57,040
Right?

982
00:54:57,050 --> 00:55:00,120
Mom, come to my apartment. We need to talk.

983
00:55:00,820 --> 00:55:01,890
Okay.

984
00:55:22,300 --> 00:55:23,980
After you meet my father,

985
00:55:23,990 --> 00:55:26,140
we'll go ahead and plan our wedding.

986
00:55:27,090 --> 00:55:30,080
You cannot marry him.

987
00:55:41,160 --> 00:55:43,650
I'm taking this to the police!

988
00:55:43,660 --> 00:55:46,620
How dare you punish my child?

989
00:55:46,630 --> 00:55:50,020
How can a teacher beat my child?

990
00:55:50,030 --> 00:55:51,320
I'm sorry.

991
00:55:51,320 --> 00:55:54,120
I apologize for what he did.

992
00:55:54,130 --> 00:55:58,520
What if something bad happens to my child?

993
00:55:58,530 --> 00:56:01,980
I'll make sure this doesn't happen again.

994
00:56:01,990 --> 00:56:04,180
I'm very sorry.

995
00:56:10,990 --> 00:56:13,120
Let's go.

996
00:56:13,700 --> 00:56:15,290
Oh, what's with the fuss?

997
00:56:17,760 --> 00:56:20,190
Are you introducing me to your future wife?

998
00:56:20,200 --> 00:56:22,390
It's Sangnam's future wife, not mine.

999
00:56:22,400 --> 00:56:24,390
My daughter in law is coming today.

1000
00:56:24,400 --> 00:56:26,940
Really? Sangnam went on a blind date?

1001
00:56:26,950 --> 00:56:30,440
He didn't. He found one on his own.

1002
00:56:30,450 --> 00:56:32,350
I never met her before.

1003
00:56:32,360 --> 00:56:35,440
And you're calling her your daughter in law?

1004
00:56:35,450 --> 00:56:37,850
I trust Sangnam,

1005
00:56:37,860 --> 00:56:40,850
and I trust Sunjeong.

1006
00:56:40,860 --> 00:56:44,680
You go ahead. The excavator mechanic is coming, so I'll catch up with you.

1007
00:56:44,700 --> 00:56:46,590
- Okay. I'll see you later.
- Yes.

1008
00:56:46,590 --> 00:56:49,350
- I'm going!
- I envy you.

1009
00:56:49,360 --> 00:56:50,620
- Bye.
- Yes, I'll see you.

1010
00:56:50,630 --> 00:56:51,520
Okay.

1011
00:56:54,030 --> 00:56:55,550
Wow!

1012
00:56:55,550 --> 00:56:56,890
That smells delicious.

1013
00:56:56,900 --> 00:56:58,850
Sunjeong, what should I wear?

1014
00:56:59,320 --> 00:57:02,620
You should wear something nice.

1015
00:57:02,630 --> 00:57:04,810
Should I wear a suit?

1016
00:57:04,820 --> 00:57:06,680
You don't have to go that far.

1017
00:57:06,700 --> 00:57:09,320
Wear a shirt and a cardigan.

1018
00:57:09,320 --> 00:57:10,810
okay.

1019
00:57:10,820 --> 00:57:15,040
I'm nervous. I hope she likes me.

1020
00:57:15,050 --> 00:57:18,210
But Daese, your hair is a bit...

1021
00:57:18,220 --> 00:57:20,140
Why? Does it look weird?

1022
00:57:20,160 --> 00:57:21,990
I think you should do your hair again.

1023
00:57:21,990 --> 00:57:25,210
Hairstyle for men is like makeup for women.

1024
00:57:25,220 --> 00:57:27,620
I don't have time to go see my barber.

1025
00:57:27,630 --> 00:57:30,420
Just go to a nearby hair salon.

1026
00:57:30,430 --> 00:57:32,820
You could get them to style your hair.

1027
00:57:34,320 --> 00:57:35,580
I got it.

1028
00:57:43,030 --> 00:57:45,790
Oh, hold on!

1029
00:57:45,800 --> 00:57:47,090
Excuse me?

1030
00:57:47,090 --> 00:57:49,510
I'd like to get my hair done. Can you do it?

1031
00:57:49,530 --> 00:57:52,090
I have to be somewhere.

1032
00:57:52,090 --> 00:57:54,740
Please. This is really important for me.

1033
00:57:54,760 --> 00:57:56,440
I can't...

1034
00:57:56,450 --> 00:57:58,910
- Oh, my...
- Please!

1035
00:57:58,930 --> 00:58:00,120
Oh, my! I can't! Hey!

1036
00:58:00,130 --> 00:58:02,750
- Come in.
- Oh, my!

1037
00:58:02,760 --> 00:58:05,920
I can't believe you. Oh...

1038
00:58:05,930 --> 00:58:07,290
Oh, my...

1039
00:58:09,760 --> 00:58:13,150
I'm in a hurry. What would you like?

1040
00:58:13,160 --> 00:58:15,220
Just make me look good.

1041
00:58:15,220 --> 00:58:16,940
Make you look good?

1042
00:58:18,300 --> 00:58:21,320
- You have curly hair?
- Yes.

1043
00:58:21,320 --> 00:58:23,510
Blow drying it to style it won't do.

1044
00:58:23,530 --> 00:58:26,320
I'd have to straighten it.

1045
00:58:26,320 --> 00:58:28,180
That's going to take time.

1046
00:58:29,320 --> 00:58:31,390
Please, I really need this.

1047
00:58:33,590 --> 00:58:34,980
I'm sorry.

1048
00:58:35,760 --> 00:58:37,350
I'll pay whatever you want,

1049
00:58:37,360 --> 00:58:41,540
so please make me look really good.

1050
00:58:42,820 --> 00:58:45,280
I think she planned this.

1051
00:58:45,300 --> 00:58:49,550
She cleaned the whole apartment and emptied the trash.

1052
00:58:49,550 --> 00:58:52,080
She even took the boys.

1053
00:58:52,090 --> 00:58:55,280
If she just went somewhere, that's okay.

1054
00:58:55,300 --> 00:58:56,750
What if it's not just that?

1055
00:58:56,760 --> 00:58:59,690
Who knows? Awful things happen these days.

1056
00:58:59,700 --> 00:59:01,450
Mom! How could you?

1057
00:59:01,450 --> 00:59:02,790
Hurry over!

1058
00:59:09,430 --> 00:59:10,420
What is it?

1059
00:59:10,430 --> 00:59:13,220
Mom, Sedal wants me to come over.

1060
00:59:13,220 --> 00:59:14,440
What's going on?

1061
00:59:14,450 --> 00:59:15,980
I don't know.

1062
00:59:15,990 --> 00:59:18,850
He said she must have planned this.

1063
00:59:18,860 --> 00:59:22,890
She cleaned the apartment and everything.

1064
00:59:22,900 --> 00:59:27,290
She took out the trash and took the boys.

1065
00:59:28,090 --> 00:59:30,890
I don't know where she fled to.

1066
00:59:30,900 --> 00:59:33,210
She fled to somewhere? Why?

1067
00:59:33,220 --> 00:59:35,120
Excuse me...

1068
00:59:35,130 --> 00:59:37,420
It's okay if she just fled,

1069
00:59:37,430 --> 00:59:41,210
but I'm afraid of her trying something stupid, like in the news.

1070
00:59:41,220 --> 00:59:42,790
You should hurry over to his apartment.

1071
00:59:42,800 --> 00:59:45,250
I'll come over right after I'm done here.

1072
00:59:45,260 --> 00:59:47,020
I think something's burning.

1073
00:59:47,030 --> 00:59:48,790
What could be burning?

1074
00:59:52,990 --> 00:59:54,750
It's not burnt.

1075
00:59:54,760 --> 00:59:56,350
But the smell...

1076
00:59:56,360 --> 00:59:57,890
I don't smell anything.

1077
00:59:57,900 --> 00:59:58,750
Go.

1078
00:59:59,430 --> 01:00:00,650
Get out.

1079
01:00:04,900 --> 01:00:06,390
Bye!

1080
01:00:06,400 --> 01:00:07,620
Hey...

1081
01:00:10,700 --> 01:00:11,720
It's burnt?

1082
01:00:11,720 --> 01:00:13,680
Yes, a bit...

1083
01:00:13,700 --> 01:00:15,520
Why didn't she pay attention?

1084
01:00:15,530 --> 01:00:17,440
Oh, man. What do I do now?

1085
01:00:17,450 --> 01:00:18,980
I want my daughter in law to like me.

1086
01:00:18,990 --> 01:00:21,520
She won't see that, so it's okay.

1087
01:00:21,530 --> 01:00:23,750
Go and change. They'll be here soon.

1088
01:00:23,760 --> 01:00:26,050
Okay. Oh, man...

1089
01:00:39,550 --> 01:00:40,810
Come in.

1090
01:00:43,860 --> 01:00:45,290
Hello.

1091
01:00:45,300 --> 01:00:47,920
Welcome. You must be nervous.

1092
01:00:47,930 --> 01:00:50,750
Yes, I can hear my heart pounding.

1093
01:00:50,760 --> 01:00:52,390
This is my first time.

1094
01:00:52,400 --> 01:00:54,040
Hey.

1095
01:00:54,050 --> 01:00:57,180
Oh, my! Miho!

1096
01:00:57,200 --> 01:00:59,720
What's going on here?

1097
01:00:59,720 --> 01:01:02,620
She's my niece. My aunt's daughter.

1098
01:01:02,630 --> 01:01:04,350
I told Miho earlier.

1099
01:01:04,900 --> 01:01:08,580
Wow, I don't believe this.

1100
01:01:10,590 --> 01:01:13,310
You didn't tell him about us, did you?

1101
01:01:13,320 --> 01:01:15,140
No, I didn't.

1102
01:01:15,160 --> 01:01:18,290
But I think you've graduated.

1103
01:01:18,300 --> 01:01:20,350
No, you have to keep teaching me.

1104
01:01:20,360 --> 01:01:22,390
And you must become my spy.

1105
01:01:22,400 --> 01:01:24,520
Okay, I will.

1106
01:01:25,160 --> 01:01:27,420
What are you whispering about?

